VGR: Entstehung, Verwendung und Veteilung

Dieses Dokument enthlt eine Auswertung der VGR Daten von der OECD.

Vorbereitung

Wir verwenden die vierteljhrlichen VGR Daten von der Organisation fr wirtschaftliche Zusammenarbeit und Entwicklung (OECD).

Die Daten knnen ber das R-Paket oecd direkt in die Software R geladen werden.

  • R-Paket oecd, Link: Search and extract data from the OECD
  • Heruntergelden werden R-Pakete mit: install.packages(OECD).
  • Geladen werden R-Pakete mit: library(OECD).

Fr die Auswertung verwenden wir vorwiegend R-Pakete die in der base environment enthalten sind.

Auerde verwenden wir auerdem folgenden R-Pakete:

  • ggplot2, Link: Create elegant data visualisations using the grammar of graphics
  • dplyr, Link: A grammar of data manipulation
  • tidyr, Link: Tidy messy data
  • lubridate, Link: Make dealing with dates a little easier
  • scales, Link: Scale functions for visualization
  • zoo, Link: S3 Infrastructure for Regular and Irregular Time Series (Zs Ordered Observations)

Hinweis: Eine benutzerfreundlichere Implementierung wrde noch mehr die Pakete dplyr, tidyr einbeziehen.

Die folgenden R-Pakete werden fr die Darstellung der Ergebnisse verwendet:

  • gridExtra, Link: Miscellaneous functions for grid graphics
  • kableExtra, Link: Construct complex table with kable and pipe syntax

Die folgenden R-Funktionen werden zur Berechnung von Anteilen, Differenzen, und Wachstumsbeitrgen verwendet.

Die folgenden R-Funktionen werden verwendet um ausgewhlte Transformationen der Daten vorzunehmen.

berblick

Beispiel: Land Deutschland, 2018

berblick

Beispiel: Land Deutschland, 2018

Die Struktur der VGR Daten der OECD kann duch die Funktion get_data_structure heruntergalden werden.

Die Daten knnen duch die Funktion get_dataset heruntergalden werden.

Entstehung

Deutschland

# > Germany, output
loc <- c("DEU") # Location: Germany
mea <- c("LNBQRSA") # Measure: Constant prices seasonal adjusted
fre <- c("Q") # Frequency: Quarterly frequency
sta.dat <- as.Date("2005-01-01") # Periods: "yyyy-mm-dd"
end.dat <- as.Date("2021-07-01")
# Note: Q1: 2020-01-01; Q2: 2020-04-01; Q3: 2020-07-01; Q3: 2020-10-01

sub <- c("B1_GA","B1GVA","B1GVB_E","B1GVF","B1GVG_I","B1GVJ","B1GVK","B1GVL","B1GVM_N","B1GVO_Q","B1GVR_U","D21_D31")
sub.agr <- c("B1GVA")
sub.ind <- c("B1GVB_E")
sub.con <- c("B1GVF")
sub.ser <- c("B1GVG_I","B1GVJ","B1GVK","B1GVL","B1GVM_N","B1GVO_Q","B1GVR_U")
sub.tls <- c("D21_D31") # taxes less subsidies on products
sub.tot <- c("B1_GA")
sub.inp.lis <- list(agr=sub.agr,
                    ind=sub.ind,
                    con=sub.con,
                    ser=sub.ser,
                    tls=sub.tls,
                    tot=sub.tot)

ger.out.01.res <- oecd.qna.fun.xx(qna.dat.00,loc,sub,mea,fre,sta.dat,end.dat,sub.inp.lis)
# > Inputs
oecd.qna.res <- ger.out.01.res

dat.inp <- oecd.qna.res$dat.04 %>%
  subset(yq(obsTime) %in% oecd.qna.res$end.dat) %>%
  subset(SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.x[-oecd.qna.res$nn])

# > Labels
lab.inp <- c("Landw.",
             "Bau",
             "Industrie",
             "Service",
             "St-Su")

# > Plot shares as pieplot
plt.x <- dat.inp %>%
  ggplot(aes(x="", y=obsValue, fill=SUBJECT)) +
  geom_bar(width = 1, stat = "identity") +
  coord_polar("y") +
  scale_fill_discrete(name="",labels=lab.inp) +
  theme(legend.position="bottom") +
  labs(x="Anteil in Prozent",y=dat.inp[1,"obsTime"],
       caption="Quelle: OECD, vierteljhrliche VGR") +
  theme(plot.caption = element_text(face="italic"))
plt.x

# > Inputs
oecd.qna.res <- ger.out.01.res

dat.inp <- oecd.qna.res$dat.04 %>%
  subset(yq(obsTime) %in% seq(as.Date(oecd.qna.res$sta.dat),as.Date(oecd.qna.res$end.dat),0.25)[-1]) %>%
  subset(SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.gx)

# > Labels
lab.inp <- c("Landw.",
             "Bau",
             "Industrie",
             "Service",
             "St-Su")

# > Plot growth contributions
plt.gx <- dat.inp %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_bar(aes(y=obsValue,x=as.yearqtr(obsTime,"%Y-Q%q"),fill=SUBJECT),position="stack",stat="identity",subset(dat.inp,SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.gx[-oecd.qna.res$nn])) +
  geom_point(aes(y=obsValue,x=as.yearqtr(obsTime,"%Y-Q%q")),subset(dat.inp,SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.gx[oecd.qna.res$nn]),size=0.5) +
  geom_line(aes(y=obsValue,x=as.yearqtr(obsTime,"%Y-Q%q")),subset(dat.inp,SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.gx[oecd.qna.res$nn]),size=0.5) +
  scale_fill_discrete(name="",labels=lab.inp) +
  theme(legend.position="bottom") +
  labs(x="",y="Vernd. in Prozentpunkte (QoQ)",
       caption="Quelle: OECD, vierteljhrliche VGR") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90),
        plot.caption = element_text(face="italic")) +  
  scale_x_yearqtr(breaks=seq(as.yearqtr(oecd.qna.res$sta.dat),as.yearqtr(oecd.qna.res$end.dat),1)[-1],
                  minor_breaks=seq(as.yearqtr(oecd.qna.res$sta.dat),as.yearqtr(oecd.qna.res$end.dat),0.25)[-1],
                  format="%Y-Q%q",
                  expand = c(0, 0))
plt.gx

Vergleich

oecd.qna.out <- function(loc,sta.dat,end.dat){
  
  
  # > Data preparation
  # loc <- c("DEU") # Location: Germany
  mea <- c("LNBQRSA") # Measure: Constant prices seasonal adjusted
  fre <- c("Q") # Frequency: Quarterly frequency
  # sta.dat <- as.Date("2005-01-01") # Periods: "yyyy-mm-dd"
  # end.dat <- as.Date("2021-07-01")
  # Note: Q1: 2020-01-01; Q2: 2020-04-01; Q3: 2020-07-01; Q3: 2020-10-01

  sub <- c("B1_GA","B1GVA","B1GVB_E","B1GVF","B1GVG_I","B1GVJ","B1GVK","B1GVL","B1GVM_N","B1GVO_Q","B1GVR_U","D21_D31")
  sub.agr <- c("B1GVA")
  sub.ind <- c("B1GVB_E")
  sub.con <- c("B1GVF")
  sub.ser <- c("B1GVG_I","B1GVJ","B1GVK","B1GVL","B1GVM_N","B1GVO_Q","B1GVR_U")
  sub.tls <- c("D21_D31") # taxes less subsidies on products
  sub.tot <- c("B1_GA")
  sub.inp.lis <- list(agr=sub.agr,
                      ind=sub.ind,
                      con=sub.con,
                      ser=sub.ser,
                      tls=sub.tls,
                      tot=sub.tot)

  out.01.res <- oecd.qna.fun.xx(qna.dat.00,loc,sub,mea,fre,sta.dat,end.dat,sub.inp.lis)
  
  
  # > Illustration share levels
  oecd.qna.res <- out.01.res

  dat.inp <- oecd.qna.res$dat.04 %>%
    subset(yq(obsTime) %in% oecd.qna.res$end.dat) %>%
    subset(SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.x[-oecd.qna.res$nn])

  # >> Labels
  lab.inp <- c("Landw.",
               "Bau",
               "Industrie",
               "Service",
               "St-Su")

  # >> Plot shares as pieplot
  plt.x <- dat.inp %>%
    ggplot(aes(x="", y=obsValue, fill=SUBJECT)) +
    geom_bar(width = 1, stat = "identity") +
    coord_polar("y") +
    scale_fill_discrete(name="",labels=lab.inp) +
    theme(legend.position="bottom") +
    labs(x="Anteil in Prozent",y=dat.inp[1,"obsTime"],
         caption="Quelle: OECD, vierteljhrliche VGR") +
    theme(plot.caption = element_text(face="italic"))
  
  
  # > Illustration growth contribution
  oecd.qna.res <- out.01.res

  dat.inp <- oecd.qna.res$dat.04 %>%
    subset(yq(obsTime) %in% seq(as.Date(oecd.qna.res$sta.dat),as.Date(oecd.qna.res$end.dat),0.25)[-1]) %>%
    subset(SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.gx)

  # >> Labels
  lab.inp <- c("Landw.",
               "Bau",
               "Industrie",
               "Service",
               "St-Su")

  # >> Plot growth contributions
  plt.gx <- dat.inp %>%
    ggplot() +
    geom_bar(aes(y=obsValue,x=as.yearqtr(obsTime,"%Y-Q%q"),fill=SUBJECT),position="stack",stat="identity",subset(dat.inp,SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.gx[-oecd.qna.res$nn])) +
    geom_point(aes(y=obsValue,x=as.yearqtr(obsTime,"%Y-Q%q")),subset(dat.inp,SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.gx[oecd.qna.res$nn]),size=0.5) +
    geom_line(aes(y=obsValue,x=as.yearqtr(obsTime,"%Y-Q%q")),subset(dat.inp,SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.gx[oecd.qna.res$nn]),size=0.5) +
    scale_fill_discrete(name="",labels=lab.inp) +
    theme(legend.position="bottom") +
    labs(x="",y="Vernd. in Prozentpunkte (QoQ)",
         caption="Quelle: OECD, vierteljhrliche VGR") +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90),
          plot.caption = element_text(face="italic")) +  
    scale_x_yearqtr(breaks=seq(as.yearqtr(oecd.qna.res$sta.dat),as.yearqtr(oecd.qna.res$end.dat),1)[-1],
                    minor_breaks=seq(as.yearqtr(oecd.qna.res$sta.dat),as.yearqtr(oecd.qna.res$end.dat),0.25)[-1],
                    format="%Y-Q%q",
                    expand = c(0, 0))
  
  ret.lis <- list(plt.x=plt.x,plt.gx=plt.gx,out.01.res=out.01.res,lab.inp=lab.inp)
  return(ret.lis)
  
}
# > Start and end date

# Note: Q1: 2020-01-01; Q2: 2020-04-01; Q3: 2020-07-01; Q3: 2020-10-01

oecd.qna.out.ger <- oecd.qna.out(loc,sta.dat,end.dat)
# > France
loc <- c("FRA")
oecd.qna.out.fra <- oecd.qna.out(loc,sta.dat,end.dat)
# > Italy
loc <- c("ITA")
oecd.qna.out.ita <- oecd.qna.out(loc,sta.dat,end.dat)
# # > USA
# loc <- c("USA")
# oecd.qna.out.usa <- oecd.qna.out(loc,sta.dat,end.dat)
# > Eurozone
loc <- c("EA19")
oecd.qna.out.ea19 <- oecd.qna.out(loc,sta.dat,end.dat)
# > United Kingdom
loc <- c("GBR")
oecd.qna.out.gbr <- oecd.qna.out(loc,sta.dat,end.dat)

oecd.qna.exp <- function(loc,sta.dat,end.dat){
  
  
  # > Data preparation
  # loc <- c("DEU") # Location: Germany
  mea <- c("LNBQRSA") # Measure: Constant prices seasonal adjusted
  fre <- c("Q") # Frequency: Quarterly frequency
  # sta.dat <- as.Date("2005-01-01") # Periods: "yyyy-mm-dd"
  # end.dat <- as.Date("2021-07-01")
  # Note: Q1: 2020-01-01; Q2: 2020-04-01; Q3: 2020-07-01; Q3: 2020-10-01

  sub <- c("B1_GE","P3","P5","B11")
  sub.con <- c("P3")
  sub.inv <- c("P5")
  sub.ext <- c("B11")
  sub.tot <- c("B1_GE")
  sub.inp.lis <- list(con=sub.con,
                      inv=sub.inv,
                      ext=sub.ext,
                      tot=sub.tot)

  exp.01.res <- oecd.qna.fun.xx(qna.dat.00,loc,sub,mea,fre,sta.dat,end.dat,sub.inp.lis)
  
  
  # > Illustration share levels
  oecd.qna.res <- exp.01.res

  dat.inp <- oecd.qna.res$dat.04 %>%
    subset(yq(obsTime) %in% oecd.qna.res$end.dat) %>%
    subset(SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.x[-oecd.qna.res$nn])

  # > Labels
  lab.inp <- c("Konsum",
               "Auenwirtschaft",
               "Investitionen")

  # > Plot shares as pieplot
  plt.x <- dat.inp %>%
    ggplot(aes(x="", y=obsValue, fill=SUBJECT)) +
    geom_bar(width = 1, stat = "identity") +
    coord_polar("y") +
    scale_fill_discrete(name="",labels=lab.inp) +
    theme(legend.position="bottom") +
    labs(x="Anteil in Prozent",y=dat.inp[1,"obsTime"],
         caption="Quelle: OECD, vierteljhrliche VGR") +
    theme(plot.caption = element_text(face="italic"))
  
  
  # > Illustration growth contribution
  oecd.qna.res <- exp.01.res

  dat.inp <- oecd.qna.res$dat.04 %>%
    subset(yq(obsTime) %in% seq(as.Date(oecd.qna.res$sta.dat),as.Date(oecd.qna.res$end.dat),0.25)[-1]) %>%
    subset(SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.gx)

  # > Labels
  lab.inp <- c("Konsum",
               "Auenwirtschaft",
               "Investitionen")

  # > Plot growth contributions
  plt.gx <- dat.inp %>%
    ggplot() +
    geom_bar(aes(y=obsValue,x=as.yearqtr(obsTime,"%Y-Q%q"),fill=SUBJECT),position="stack",stat="identity",subset(dat.inp,SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.gx[-oecd.qna.res$nn])) +
    geom_point(aes(y=obsValue,x=as.yearqtr(obsTime,"%Y-Q%q")),subset(dat.inp,SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.gx[oecd.qna.res$nn]),size=0.5) +
    geom_line(aes(y=obsValue,x=as.yearqtr(obsTime,"%Y-Q%q")),subset(dat.inp,SUBJECT %in% oecd.qna.res$sub.gx[oecd.qna.res$nn]),size=0.5) +
    scale_fill_discrete(name="",labels=lab.inp) +
    theme(legend.position="bottom") +
    labs(x="",y="Vernd. in Prozentpunkte (QoQ)",
         caption="Quelle: OECD, vierteljhrliche VGR") +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90),
          plot.caption = element_text(face="italic")) +  
    scale_x_yearqtr(breaks=seq(as.yearqtr(oecd.qna.res$sta.dat),as.yearqtr(oecd.qna.res$end.dat),1)[-1],
                    minor_breaks=seq(as.yearqtr(oecd.qna.res$sta.dat),as.yearqtr(oecd.qna.res$end.dat),0.25)[-1],
                    format="%Y-Q%q",
                    expand = c(0, 0))
  
  ret.lis <- list(plt.x=plt.x,plt.gx=plt.gx,exp.01.res=exp.01.res,lab.inp=lab.inp)
  return(ret.lis)
  
}
